HEADWORD: Wekau
<hw>We"kau</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
small New Zealand owl (<spn>Sceloglaux albifacies</spn>). It has short
wings and long legs, and lives chiefly on the ground.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

